  "prompt": "What is green building?",
  "response": "Green building, also known as sustainable or high-performance building, is an approach to construction and design that minimizes environmental impact and maximizes resource efficiency throughout a building's lifecycle. Key characteristics include:\n\n1. Energy efficiency\n- Reduced energy consumption\n- Use of renewable energy sources\n- Efficient heating and cooling systems\n\n2. Water conservation\n- Low-flow fixtures\n- Rainwater harvesting\n- Efficient irrigation systems\n\n3. Sustainable materials\n- Recycled or renewable materials\n- Locally sourced materials\n- Low-emission materials\n\n4. Waste reduction\n- Minimizing construction waste\n- Recycling and reusing materials\n- Efficient waste management\n\n5. Indoor environmental quality\n- Improved air quality\n- Natural lighting\n- Non-toxic materials\n\n6. Site selection and development\n- Minimizing environmental disruption\n- Preserving natural landscapes\n- Reducing urban heat island effect\n\n7. Long-term sustainability\n- Reduced operational costs\n- Lower maintenance expenses\n- Extended building lifespan\n\nGreen building aims to create structures that are environmentally responsible, resource-efficient, and beneficial to human health and well-being. Certification systems like LEED (Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design) provide standards for green building practices.",
